# Vesyoly, Shovgenovsky District, Republic of Adygea

}}
Vesyoly () is a rural locality (a khutor) in Zarevskoye Rural Settlement of Shovgenovsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 249 as of 2018. There are three streets.
Geography
Vesyoly is located  southeast of Khakurinokhabl (the district's administrative centre) by road. Chernyshyov is the nearest rural locality.
